  "decision_agency": null,
  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed development, by virtue of its inadequate functional floor area due to the low floor-to-ceiling heights, would result in substandard and inappropriate accommodation incapable of meeting the reasonable needs of occupiers contrary to Section 12 of the National Planning Policy Framework (2024), to Policies D3 and D6 of the London Plan (2021), to Policies CP4 and CP30 of the Enfield Core Strategy (2010), to Policies DMD5 and DMD8 of the Enfield Development Management Document (2014), and the Housing Design Standards London Plan Guidance (2023).",
    "The proposed conversion would result in the loss of a 4-bedroom family dwelling and fails to provide adequate compensatory family accommodation, leading to a net reduction in family housing within the borough. This outcome undermines the Council's strategic objective to increase the supply of larger (3+ bedroom) units, which are essential to meeting the housing needs of families. The proposal is therefore contrary to Section 5 of the National Planning Policy Framework (2024), Policy GG4 of the London Plan (2021), Policy CP5 of the Core Strategy (2010), Policies DMD4 and DMD5 of the Development Management Document (2014), and the Council's Strategic Housing Market Assessment (SHMA 2015)."
  ],
